11:
Went a little wild while you were at it
too.
16:
Gotta pace yourself, or else you'll
end up falling flat on your face
again!
22:
Nuh-uh! I can still keep going! Let's
gooo!
33: Ugh... I did it again, didn't I?
37: It's okay, don't worry about it.
41:
The most important thing is that you
are unharmed.
47: Ahaha, I'm such a screw-up, huh?
53:
A-ahaha, anyway, this is just
another day in my life! Sorry about
the griping!
56:
Floretta, you were born on a
northern island in your world, right?
60:
Yeah, a volcanic one in the northern
part of Oceanus. Why?
63:
I just wanted to learn more about
you.
68:
Now that Stella mentions it, you
don't really talk much about
yourself, huh?
73:
I don't mind, but... I'm not that
interesting of a person.
76:
We're not here to judge. Besides,
we've got some time to kill.
80:
Actually, why don't we go do
something fun?
89:
Hmm, how about fishing? Here,
come take over.
100: Uhhhh, do I just... hold the rod?
103:
Yep, that's all you gotta do right
now! Is this your first time?
107:
Yeah... I've never really had anyone
show me how to before.
111:
Eh, it's something you can wing,
honestly.
116:
Alk, am I stacking the firewood
correctly?
122:
*sigh* Is it really okay for me to be
relaxing like this?
124: Mmm, at least the wind feels nice—
141: This isn't good. At this rate...
151:
You sure this is your first time? This
thing's HUGE!
169:
So you inherited your sword from an
alchemist.
172:
A whimsical one, at that. Didn't even
tell me how to use the thing, so I got
owned the first time I tried it out...
176:
I know you said you're from a
northern island. Was it cold?
179:
It sure was. Covered in snow all year
round. Apparently in the past, it was
just barren mountain peaks as far
as the eye could see.
181:
My village relied on a big boiler to
keep things running, but because of
that, we couldn't support too many
people. It was a pretty hard place to
live.
184:
Huh... Life must've been really
different there.
188:
Why did you decide to leave home,
Floretta?
197:
I don't remember, but I get the
feeling I was running away.
203:
Everything. I run from all my
problems...
204:
Just like when I sunk the Captain's
ship.
207: Ahaha... I quit then and there.
210:
It wasn't like I didn't try. I know I'm
less competent than everyone else,
so I did my best.
211:
But my best is never enough to keep
people from leaving me.
220:
That's right. You're plenty amazing
already, in my humble opinion.
222: Yes. That large fish is proof.
227: Gosh... I don't know what to say.
230:
We're here for you whenever you
need us.
233:
Ahaha... I might actually take you up
on that.
236:
Especially Alk. He'll do whatever you
want.
246:
Duly noted. Thanks, you two. This
means a lot to me.
